-- COVERAGE GAP (found 2026-07-13, task T28): every `fn_multiclause_*` fixture used
-- INT literal heads or constructor heads.  A multi-clause function whose clause
-- columns are STRING literals routes emitClauseTree's switch through a different
-- head (`HLit (LString …)`) — string equality tests, not an i31 icmp — and nothing
-- in the corpus pinned it.  (It works; it was simply never gated.)
-- code "red" = 1 ; code "green" = 2 ; code "blue" = 3 ; code _ = 0
-- Also pins a 2-column string clause (`pair`), so the multi-column matrix sees
-- string literals in more than the leftmost column.
code "red" = 1
code "green" = 2
code "blue" = 3
code _ = 0

pair "a" "b" = 10
pair "a" _ = 20
pair _ "b" = 30
pair _ _ = 40

main = code "green" * 1000 + code "red" * 100 + code "nope" * 10 + pair "a" "b" + pair "a" "z" + pair "z" "b" + pair "z" "z"
